We kept hearing good things about the paella here.  Paella seems like a topic that inspires passionate debate among the Spanish, whether what you are eating is technically paella, or where are the acceptable places to eat paella.  I like the passion.The paella here was alright, but not my favorite.  I would have to say that the best paella that I've ever had is still stateside.  We ordered the mixed paella, which had chicken and seafood in it.  Given another chance, I would have ordered the seafood only paella (I was hoping the mix had sausage in it).  The dish was a little salty for my taste, but other than that, it had plenty of seafood in it.We also tried the honey eggplant dish.  Sticks of eggplant lightly fried and drizzled with honey.  The honey was was the real star of this dish, you could still taste the flowers in the honey, it had a complex flavor.  The eggplant itself was, again, too salty for my taste.
